Build ID: M20071023-1652

Steps To Reproduce:
1. I have an external Makefile and I am using gcc on Linux
2. Start a clean build
3. Build will fail and stop always at the same point (source file); Error messagebox will pop up
4. Console output: make[1]: write error


More information:

A build outside of Eclipse *never* fails. The same problem occurs with two projects. It is reproducible if I do a make clean before the actual build. If I restart the build after the failure the build continues flawlessly.
